urred in a short time from $\\sim 9.2$ Hz\n(C) to $\\sim 4.8$ Hz (B). The energy spectral analysis for the other two\ntransitions shows that when type-C QPO is present, the Comptonization flux is\nhigher, the spectrum is harder and the inner radius of disk changes\ninsignificantly. We suggest that type-C QPOs probably originate from relatively\nstronger jets or corona.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Aug 2022 08:28:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-26"}
